short_description: low in calories, with no fat, and no cholesterol and no salt
product_description: Exceptionally delicious, Libby's Naturals Whole Kernel Sweet Corn is the tasty sweet descendant of maize - a "New World" vegetable. Sweet corn is a variety of maize that naturally has a higher sugar content - making it "sweeter tasting." Libby's Naturals Whole Kernel Sweet Corn is picked while still young, in the "milk stage," to ensure the most enjoyable eating, and then prepared within hours and just miles from where it was grown to seal in Farm Fresh Goodness for a delicious flavor, crisp texture and vibrantly bright golden yellow color. We put just our finest Whole Kernel Sweet Corn in every can. It is no wonder that Libby's canned corn has been the favorite of generations as a splash of color side-dish, snack or ingredient in favorite recipes. Libby's Naturals Whole Kernel Sweet Corn is made with 100% Sweet Corn for a naturally sweet flavor, bright golden yellow color and just-off-the-cob crispness. A Low Fat food, No Added Sugar (though some sugar exists in sweet corn naturally), No Preservatives. Wheat Free. Part of a Healthy lifestyle. Farm-to-Table - Libby's Naturals Whole Kernel Sweet Corn is cultivated in the U.S. heartland by multi-generational, U.S. farmers on family-owned farms located primarily in the fertile regions of Illinois, Minnesota, Iowa or Wisconsin. This is the prime growing region for Sweet Corn with its fertile soil and ideal combination of sun and rain fall. Once harvested our corn travels just miles and is prepared in state-of-the art, FDA inspected facilities sealing in Farm Fresh Goodness within hours of being picked! Libby's Naturals Sweet Corn is seasonally grown and harvested fresh at the peak of ripeness. "Seasonally grown" means that every year, typically in May, we plant our Sweet Corn and then let it grow and mature through the summer months until August when the harvest begins. In a typical year all of our corn is harvested and prepared, sealing in its naturally sweet flavor and bright golden yellow color by October.

product_description: Green Giant is dedicated to growing the highest quality vegetables around the world. Green Giant frozen vegetables are flash frozen very near where they’re harvested to quickly lock in their goodness. Our vegetables are then packaged at one of our expert packaging facilities and shipped to a grocery store near you. Green Giant canned vegetables are also canned near the farms where they are harvested. We handpick our packaging partners to ensure our vegetables are promptly packaged, sealing in the highest quality before delivering all that goodness to you. Our frozen vegetables are packaged in: Illinois, California, Minnesota, Idaho, Washington, and Mexico. Our canned vegetables also undergo the canning process near where they are grown: in Minnesota, Idaho, Wisconsin, New York, the Netherlands, and Peru. Our vegetables are non-GMO. Green Giant uses only non-GMO seed when planting our vegetables. Some ingredients in our Sauced and Seasoned products may contain GMOs. Ingredients that may contain GMOs are: corn, corn oil, corn starch, corn syrup, corn syrup solids, soy oil, soy powder, soy lecithin, hydrolyzed vegetable protein, hydrolyzed plant protein, cotton seed oil, canola oil, vegetable oil sugar, and squash. While Green Giant uses only non-GMO seed when planting our vegetables, we do not test our ingredients in seasonings and sauces for GMOs, and we do not purchase verified non-GMO ingredients.
